re Mobile Apps Available to Assist With Company Registration in India?<br><br></h2>\n<p data-start=\"5391\" data-end=\"5514\">While MCA itself doesnâ€™t have a full registration app, many <strong data-start=\"5451\" data-end=\"5513\">digital service providers offer mobile-friendly dashboards</strong>.</p>\n<p data-start=\"5516\" data-end=\"5536\">People often search:</p>\n<ul data-start=\"5537\" data-end=\"5609\">\n<li data-start=\"5537\" data-end=\"5573\">\n<p data-start=\"5539\" data-end=\"5573\"><em data-start=\"5539\" data-end=\"5573\">â€œcompany registration app Indiaâ€</em></p>\n</li>\n<li data-start=\"5574\" data-end=\"5609\">\n<p data-start=\"5576\" data-end=\"5609\"><em data-start=\"5576\" data-end=\"5609\">â€œregister company using mobileâ€</em></p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-start=\"5611\" data-end=\"5663\">Ensure your platform experience is mobile-optimised.<br><br></p>\n<h2 data-start=\"5670\" data-end=\"5751\">11. What Is the Average Timeline for Company Registration Using Online Portals?<br><br></h2>\n<p data-start=\"5753\" data-end=\"5822\">The <strong data-start=\"5757\" data-end=\"5818\">average timeline for online company registration in India</strong> is:</p>\n<p data-start=\"5824\" data-end=\"5852\"><strong data-start=\"5826\" data-end=\"5847\">7â€“10 working days</strong>, if:</p>\n<ul data-start=\"5853\" data-end=\"5939\">\n<li data-start=\"5853\" data-end=\"5878\">\n<p data-start=\"5855\" data-end=\"5878\">a. Documents are correct</p>\n</li>\n<li data-start=\"5879\" data-end=\"5907\">\n<p data-start=\"5881\" data-end=\"5907\">b. Name is approved quickly</p>\n</li>\n<li data-start=\"5908\" data-end=\"5939\">\n<p data-start=\"5910\" data-end=\"5939\">c. DSC is issued without delay</p></li></ul>', 'EnsureKar Editorial Team', 'content@ensurekar.com', 'Ensurekar is a trusted compliance and business consultancy helping startups and businesses with company registration, taxation, and legal services across India.', 'published', 0, '1766480912144_fo3kikegjf5.png', '/images/upload/blogImage/1766480912144_fo3kikegjf5.png', '[\"company registration India private limited company startup registration online company incorporation MCA registration\",\"company registration\",\"private limited company\",\"startup registration\",\"online company incorporation MCA registration\",\"MCA registration\",\"online company incorporation\",\"India private limited company registration online\",\"company registration online\",\"company registration India private limited company startup registration online\"]', '2025-12-23 14:40:00', '2025-12-23 03:38:30', '2025-12-23 03:38:30', 0, 'How to Register a Private Limited Company Online in India (2025)', 'Step-by-step guide on how to register a private limited company online in India. Learn cost, documents, timelines, and best online company registration services.'),
(22, 'Got a Scary Income Tax Alert? 5 Things You Must Know Before You Panic', 'income-tax-alert-processing-on-hold-risk-management', 'Received an SMS from the Income Tax Department saying your return is “on hold” due to Risk Management? Don’t panic. Here’s what the alert really means, why it happens, deadlines to watch, and what you should do next.', '<h2 data-start=\"412\" data-end=\"471\">That SMS From the Income Tax Department Can Shake Anyone</h2>\n<p data-start=\"473\" data-end=\"621\">For most taxpayers, income tax is something you deal with once a year and then forget about. You file your return, wait for the refund, and move on.<br><br></p>\n<p data-start=\"623\" data-end=\"743\">So when your phone suddenly lights up with an SMS from the <strong data-start=\"682\" data-end=\"707\">Income Tax Department</strong>, anxiety kicks in almost instantly.</p>\n<p data-start=\"745\" data-end=\"926\">Recently, many taxpayers have received a message saying that their <strong data-start=\"812\" data-end=\"925\">income tax return for AY 2025–26 has been “put on hold” due to a discrepancy identified under Risk Management</strong>.<br><br></p>\n<p data-start=\"928\" data-end=\"976\">The wording feels serious.<br data-start=\"954\" data-end=\"957\">\nAlmost threatening.</p>\n<p data-start=\"978\" data-end=\"1030\">But the reality is far less dramatic than it sounds.</p>\n<h2 data-start=\"1037\" data-end=\"1086\">This Is Not a Scrutiny. It’s an Early Warning.<br><br></h2>\n<p data-start=\"1088\" data-end=\"1172\">The most important thing to understand is this:<br data-start=\"1135\" data-end=\"1138\">\n<strong data-start=\"1138\" data-end=\"1171\"><br>this is not a scrutiny notice</strong>.</p>\n<p data-start=\"1174\" data-end=\"1440\">The department has not started an investigation into your income or your financial affairs. What has happened is much simpler. The automated systems that process returns have detected something that doesn’t fully add up — usually related to the refund being claimed.<br><br></p>\n<p data-start=\"1442\" data-end=\"1552\">Instead of issuing the refund first and checking later, the system pauses the return and sends you a heads-up.<br><br></p>\n<p data-start=\"1554\" data-end=\"1604\">Think of it as a <strong data-start=\"1571\" data-end=\"1603\">yellow signal, not a red one</strong>.</p>\n<p data-start=\"1606\" data-end=\"1689\">It’s the department’s way of saying, <em data-start=\"1643\" data-end=\"1689\">“Before we move ahead, please double-check.”</em></p>\n<h2 data-start=\"1696\" data-end=\"1745\">Why So Many Returns Are Suddenly Being Flagged</h2>\n<p data-start=\"1747\" data-end=\"1853\">This wave of alerts is not random. It reflects a larger shift in how income tax returns are now processed.</p>\n<p data-start=\"1855\" data-end=\"2111\">The tax department today matches your return with multiple data sources in real time — salary details, bank interest, investment information, and transaction records. When your return doesn’t align with what their systems already know, it triggers a pause.</p>\n<p data-start=\"2113\" data-end=\"2177\">The most common reason behind this pause is surprisingly simple.<br><br></p>\n<p data-start=\"2179\" data-end=\"2224\">A misunderstanding of the <strong data-start=\"2205\" data-end=\"2223\">New Tax Regime</strong>.</p>\n<h2 data-start=\"2231\" data-end=\"2277\">The New Tax Regime Has Become a Silent Trap</h2>\n<p data-start=\"2279\" data-end=\"2471\">Many taxpayers opted for the New Tax Regime because of its lower tax rates. What often gets overlooked, however, is that <strong data-start=\"2400\" data-end=\"2470\">most deductions and allowances are not permitted under this regime</strong>.<br><br></p>\n<p data-start=\"2473\" data-end=\"2628\">Despite this, people continue to claim benefits such as House Rent Allowance, dress allowance, children’s education allowance, and other salary exemptions.<br><br></p>\n<p data-start=\"2630\" data-end=\"2799\">When these deductions are claimed under the New Tax Regime, the system flags the return almost immediately — especially if it results in a very high or near-100% refund.</p>\n<p data-start=\"2801\" data-end=\"2910\">This issue has been particularly common among salaried individuals earning between <strong data-start=\"2884\" data-end=\"2909\">?10 lakh and ?20 lakh</strong>.</p>\n<p data-start=\"2912\" data-end=\"3030\">If such mistakes are not corrected voluntarily, the chances of receiving a formal notice later increase significantly.<br><br></p>\n<h2 data-start=\"3037\" data-end=\"3072\">It’s Not Always About Deductions</h2>\n<p data-start=\"3074\" data-end=\"3197\">While errors under the New Tax Regime are the most frequent trigger, they are not the only reason returns are being paused.</p>\n<p data-start=\"3199\" data-end=\"3394\">In many cases, the issue is an income mismatch. Interest income, dividends, or other transactions appearing in the <strong data-start=\"3314\" data-end=\"3352\">Annual Information Statement (AIS)</strong> may not have been included in the return.<br><br></p>\n<p data-start=\"3396\" data-end=\"3554\">Sometimes, the tax deducted at source shown in the return doesn’t match <strong data-start=\"3468\" data-end=\"3481\">Form 26AS</strong>. In other situations, deductions are claimed without sufficient backing.</p>\n<p data-start=\"3556\" data-end=\"3668\">None of this automatically implies wrongdoing. It simply means the system wants clarification before proceeding.</p>\n<h2 data-start=\"3675\" data-end=\"3731\">The Email That Never Arrives (And What to Do Instead)</h2>\n<p data-start=\"3733\" data-end=\"3896\">The SMS usually states that details of the discrepancy will be sent to your registered email address. In reality, many taxpayers never receive any follow-up email.<br><br></p>\n<p data-start=\"3898\" data-end=\"3971\">This creates confusion, because it’s hard to fix a problem you can’t see.</p>\n<p data-start=\"3973\" data-end=\"4058\">If you find yourself in this situation, don’t rush into revising your return blindly.</p>\n<p data-start=\"4060\" data-end=\"4272\">Log in to the income tax portal and keep an eye on your <strong data-start=\"4116\" data-end=\"4128\">Worklist</strong> and <strong data-start=\"4133\" data-end=\"4150\">e-Proceedings</strong> sections. In some cases, the department places an interactive message there asking you to confirm or deny a refund claim.</p>\n<p data-start=\"4274\" data-end=\"4365\">It’s also worth checking your spam folder. Official emails often end up there unexpectedly.<br><br></p>\n<h2 data-start=\"4372\" data-end=\"4413\">Time Is on Your Side — But Not Forever</h2>\n<p data-start=\"4415\" data-end=\"4510\">If, after reviewing your return, you identify an error, there is still a safe window to fix it.</p>\n<p data-start=\"4512\" data-end=\"4596\">You can file a <strong data-start=\"4527\" data-end=\"4568\">revised return up to 31 December 2025</strong> without paying any penalty.</p>\n<p data-start=\"4598\" data-end=\"4780\">After that, the only option available is filing an <strong data-start=\"4649\" data-end=\"4675\">Updated Return (ITR-U)</strong>. This comes at a cost. The law imposes an additional tax of <strong data-start=\"4736\" data-end=\"4758\">25% on the tax due</strong>, along with interest.</p>\n<p data-start=\"4782\" data-end=\"4864\">In simple terms, correcting a mistake now is far cheaper than correcting it later.</p>\n<h2 data-start=\"4871\" data-end=\"4913\">How to Review Your Return the Right Way</h2>\n<p data-start=\"4915\" data-end=\"4989\">Before taking any action, it’s important to verify your numbers carefully.<br><br></p>\n<p data-start=\"4991\" data-end=\"5149\">Compare your filed return with three key documents: <strong data-start=\"5043\" data-end=\"5056\">Form 26AS</strong>, the <strong data-start=\"5062\" data-end=\"5100\">Annual Information Statement (AIS)</strong>, and the <strong data-start=\"5110\" data-end=\"5148\">Taxpayer Information Summary (TIS)</strong>.<br><br></p>\n<p data-start=\"5151\" data-end=\"5299\">These documents reflect what the tax department already knows about your income. Your return should tell the exact same story — no more and no less.<br><br></p>\n<p data-start=\"5301\" data-end=\"5534\">If you discover a genuine mistake, revise your return once and do it carefully. If everything checks out, patience is often the best response. In many cases, the department processes the return once internal verification is complete.</p>\n<p data-start=\"5536\" data-end=\"5650\">Avoid revising your return multiple times. Repeated changes create uncertainty and can draw unnecessary attention.</p>\n<hr data-start=\"5652\" data-end=\"5655\">\n<h2 data-start=\"5657\" data-end=\"5698\">The Bigger Message Behind These Alerts</h2>\n<p data-start=\"5700\" data-end=\"5748\">This isn’t just about one SMS or one tax return.<br><br></p>\n<p data-start=\"5750\" data-end=\"5906\">It’s a clear signal that the era of <strong data-start=\"5786\" data-end=\"5815\">“file and forget” is over</strong>. Income tax compliance is becoming more data-driven, more automated, and far more precise.<br><br></p>\n<p data-start=\"5908\" data-end=\"6012\">The good news is that honest taxpayers who verify their returns and respond calmly have nothing to fear.<br><br></p>\n<p data-start=\"6014\" data-end=\"6105\">Don’t panic.<br data-start=\"6026\" data-end=\"6029\">\nDon’t ignore the alert.<br data-start=\"6052\" data-end=\"6055\">\nUse it as a reminder to be accurate and proactive.</p>\n<p data-start=\"6107\" data-end=\"6191\">In today’s tax environment, <strong data-start=\"6135\" data-end=\"6190\">clarity and diligence are your strongest safeguards</strong></p>', 'EnsureKar Tax & Compliance Team', 'support@ensurekar.com', 'EnsureKar helps individuals and businesses navigate income tax, compliance, and regulatory matters with clarity, accuracy, and expert support across India.', 'published', 0, '1766654103201_tk28dxylc9n.jpeg', '/images/upload/blogImage/1766654103201_tk28dxylc9n.jpeg', '[\"Income Tax Notice\",\"ITR Processing On Hold\",\"Risk Management Income Tax\",\"Revised Return\",\"AIS Form 26AS\"]', '2025-12-25 17:09:00', '2025-12-25 03:45:02', '2025-12-25 06:04:34', 0, ' Income Tax Alert: ITR Processing On Hold? What It Means & What to Do', 'Received an income tax alert saying your return is on hold due to Risk Management? Learn why it happens, common mistakes, deadlines, and the exact steps you should take.'),
(26, 'India’s Aviation Shake-Up: 3 New Airlines Set to Challenge the IndiGo–Air India Duopoly', 'india-aviation-new-airlines-indigo-air-india-duopoly', 'India has approved three new airlines—Shankh Air, Al Hind Air, and FlyExpress—in a strategic move to reduce dependence on the IndiGo–Air India duopoly. This development could reshape competition, fares, and regional connectivity in one of the world’s fastest-growing aviation markets.', '<p data-start=\"677\" data-end=\"1081\">India’s domestic aviation market is on the brink of a significant shift. After years of dominance by a handful of large carriers, the government has cleared three new airlines to enter the sector—Shankh Air, Al Hind Air, and FlyExpress. The approvals signal more than just new players taking off; they reflect a policy-level push to make India’s skies more competitive, resilient, and passenger-friendly.<br><br></p>\n<p data-start=\"1083\" data-end=\"1171\">For travellers, investors, and industry watchers, this moment marks an inflexion point.<br><br></p>\n<h3 data-start=\"1173\" data-end=\"1211\"><b>A Clear Signal from the Government</b></h3>\n<p data-start=\"1213\" data-end=\"1585\">The Ministry of Civil Aviation has granted No Objection Certificates (NOCs) to all three airlines, clearing an essential regulatory hurdle before they move toward full operational approval. Civil Aviation Minister K. Ram Mohan Naidu has confirmed that the government has engaged directly with the promoters, underscoring official intent to widen competition in the sector.</p>\n<p data-start=\"1587\" data-end=\"1832\">Shankh Air, which received its NOC earlier, is expected to begin commercial operations around 2026. Al Hind Air and FlyExpress have now joined the list, with plans reportedly focused on a mix of underserved regional routes and key trunk sectors.</p>\n<p data-start=\"1834\" data-end=\"2012\">While receiving an NOC does not guarantee success, it is a strong first step—and one that the government does not grant lightly in today’s tightly regulated aviation environment.<br><br></p>\n<h3 data-start=\"2014\" data-end=\"2053\"><b>Why This Approval Matters Right Now<br><br></b></h3>\n<p data-start=\"2055\" data-end=\"2362\">The timing of these approvals is not accidental. India recently witnessed large-scale disruptions following operational issues at IndiGo, resulting in mass cancellations and delays. The incident reignited public discussion around a long-standing concern: India’s heavy dependence on just two airline groups.</p>\n<p data-start=\"2364\" data-end=\"2685\">Industry estimates suggest that IndiGo and the Air India group together command well over 90% of the domestic market. In such a concentrated environment, even a single airline’s disruption can ripple across the entire system—driving up fares, shrinking seat availability, and leaving passengers with limited alternatives.</p>\n<p data-start=\"2687\" data-end=\"2836\">By allowing new airlines to enter, the government appears to be addressing this structural risk head-on rather than relying only on short-term fixes.<br><br></p>\n<h3 data-start=\"2838\" data-end=\"2874\"><b>What Could Change for Passengers<br><br></b></h3>\n<p data-start=\"2876\" data-end=\"3141\">If these new airlines manage to move from approval to sustainable operations, passengers could begin to see tangible benefits over time. Increased competition often leads to better route coverage, especially on sectors currently served by only one dominant carrier.</p>\n<p data-start=\"3143\" data-end=\"3454\">There is also the possibility of more stable pricing on certain routes, particularly where additional capacity is introduced. For Tier-2 and Tier-3 cities, regionally focused airlines could improve connectivity and support initiatives like UDAN, which aim to make air travel more accessible beyond major metros.</p>\n<p data-start=\"3456\" data-end=\"3601\">That said, expectations must remain realistic. Indian aviation has seen many ambitious entries over the years, and not all of them have survived.<br><b><br></b><img src=\"/images/upload/blogImage/1766666745767_jhc5kla47gr.jpg\"><br></p>\n<h3 data-start=\"3603\" data-end=\"3642\"><b>The Hard Reality of Indian Aviation<br><br></b></h3>\n<p data-start=\"3644\" data-end=\"3906\">History offers a sobering reminder. Airlines such as Kingfisher, Jet Airways, Go First, and several regional players entered the market with promise but struggled under the weight of high fuel costs, aggressive price competition, debt, and regulatory complexity.</p>\n<p data-start=\"3908\" data-end=\"4199\">Analysts quoted across major business publications agree that while approvals are encouraging, long-term success will depend on fundamentals. Strong capitalisation, disciplined cost control, smart fleet choices, and realistic route planning will matter far more than branding or launch buzz.</p>\n<p data-start=\"4201\" data-end=\"4381\">Partnerships, code-share agreements, and focused regional strategies may offer a more sustainable path than attempting to directly replicate the business models of existing giants.<br><b><br></b></p>\n<h3 data-start=\"4383\" data-end=\"4424\"><b>Why This Move Matters Beyond Aviation<br><br></b></h3>\n<p data-start=\"4426\" data-end=\"4670\">Beyond airlines and airports, this development offers insight into India’s broader competition policy approach. Instead of breaking up dominant players, the state is choosing to lower entry barriers and accelerate approvals for new challengers.</p>\n<p data-start=\"4672\" data-end=\"4951\">It reflects a regulatory mindset that prioritises market resilience and consumer choice, especially in sectors where concentration poses systemic risks. For founders, investors, and policy observers, the journey of Shankh Air, Al Hind Air, and FlyExpress will be closely watched.<br><br></p>\n<p data-start=\"4953\" data-end=\"5143\">Their progress—from NOC to Air Operator Certificate, and eventually to sustainable operations—will reveal how supportive India’s regulatory and financial ecosystem truly is for new entrants.<br><br></p>\n<h3 data-start=\"5145\" data-end=\"5172\"><b>A Market Worth Watching<br><br></b></h3>\n<p data-start=\"5174\" data-end=\"5341\">India is already one of the fastest-growing aviation markets in the world. Whether it can sustainably support more than two dominant carriers remains an open question.<br><br></p>\n<p data-start=\"5343\" data-end=\"5593\">What is clear, however, is that the government has signalled its intent. The skies are opening up, competition is being encouraged, and the coming years will determine whether these new airlines can convert regulatory approval into long-term success.<br><br></p>\n<p data-start=\"5595\" data-end=\"5665\">For passengers, that alone is a development worth paying attention to.</p>', 'EnsureKar Editorial Team', 'connect@ensurekar.com', 'The EnsureKar Editorial Team writes on business, taxation, compliance, policy, and regulatory developments that impact startups, professionals, and growing enterprises across India.', 'published', 1, '1766666678085_9frt272icyi.jpg', '/images/upload/blogImage/1766666678085_9frt272icyi.jpg', '[\"Indian aviation, new airlines India, Shankh Air, Al Hind Air, FlyExpress, IndiGo, Air India, aviation policy, competition India\",\"Indian aviation\",\"new airlines India\",\"Shankh Air\",\"Al Hind Air\",\"FlyExpress\",\"IndiGo\",\"Air India\",\"aviation policy\",\"competition India\"]', '2025-12-26 20:00:00', '2025-12-25 07:13:07', '2025-12-25 07:15:46', 0, 'India Approves 3 New Airlines to Challenge IndiGo–Air India Duopoly', 'India has approved Shankh Air, Al Hind Air and FlyExpress to enter the aviation market. Here’s what it means for competition, fares, and passengers.'),
(27, 'PAN–Aadhaar Linking Deadline on December 31, 2025: How to Link, Check Status & Avoid Inoperative PAN', 'pan-aadhaar-linking-deadline-december-31-2025', 'The PAN–Aadhaar linking deadline is December 31, 2025. Failure to link will make your PAN inoperative and disrupt income tax filing, refunds, and banking services. Here’s a complete step-by-step guide to linking, checking status, and fixing mismatched details.', '<p data-start=\"743\" data-end=\"1098\">The countdown has officially begun for PAN–Aadhaar linking. As reported by <strong data-start=\"818\" data-end=\"837\">Hindustan Times</strong>, taxpayers who have not yet linked their PAN with Aadhaar and paid the applicable late fee have only <strong data-start=\"939\" data-end=\"958\">seven days left</strong>, with the final deadline set for <strong data-start=\"992\" data-end=\"1013\">December 31, 2025</strong>. Missing this deadline could result in serious financial and compliance disruptions.<br><br></p>\n<p data-start=\"1100\" data-end=\"1288\">If your PAN becomes inoperative, you may face difficulties in filing income tax returns, receiving refunds, completing banking transactions, or even using PAN as a valid identity document.<br><br></p>\n<h4 data-start=\"1290\" data-end=\"1335\"><strong data-start=\"1295\" data-end=\"1335\">Why PAN–Aadhaar Linking Is Mandatory<br><br></strong></h4>\n<p data-start=\"1337\" data-end=\"1608\">According to the Income Tax Department, it is mandatory for <strong data-start=\"1397\" data-end=\"1473\">all existing PAN holders who were allotted PAN on or before July 1, 2017</strong>, to link their PAN with Aadhaar. This requirement applies to both registered and unregistered users on the Income Tax e-Filing portal.<br><br></p>\n<p data-start=\"1610\" data-end=\"1658\">The official income tax portal clearly states:<br><br></p>\n<blockquote data-start=\"1659\" data-end=\"1777\">\n<p data-start=\"1661\" data-end=\"1777\">“For existing PAN holders, who were allotted PAN on or before 01-07-2017, it is mandatory to link PAN with Aadhaar.”</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p data-start=\"1779\" data-end=\"1923\">For <strong data-start=\"1783\" data-end=\"1805\">new PAN applicants</strong>, Aadhaar-based authentication is already compulsory at the time of application, making the linking process automatic.<br><br></p>\n<h4 data-start=\"1925\" data-end=\"1981\"><strong data-start=\"1930\" data-end=\"1981\">What Happens If You Don’t Link PAN with Aadhaar<br><br></strong></h4>\n<p data-start=\"1983\" data-end=\"2100\">If PAN–Aadhaar linking is not completed by December 31, 2025, your PAN will become <strong data-start=\"2066\" data-end=\"2081\">inoperative</strong>. This may lead to:<br><br></p>\n<ul data-start=\"2102\" data-end=\"2303\">\n<li data-start=\"2102\" data-end=\"2142\">\n<p data-start=\"2104\" data-end=\"2142\">Inability to file Income Tax Returns</p>\n</li>\n<li data-start=\"2143\" data-end=\"2180\">\n<p data-start=\"2145\" data-end=\"2180\">Delay or rejection of tax refunds</p>\n</li>\n<li data-start=\"2181\" data-end=\"2231\">\n<p data-start=\"2183\" data-end=\"2231\">Problems in opening or operating bank accounts</p>\n</li>\n<li data-start=\"2232\" data-end=\"2257\">\n<p data-start=\"2234\" data-end=\"2257\">Higher TDS deductions</p>\n</li>\n<li data-start=\"2258\" data-end=\"2303\">\n<p data-start=\"2260\" data-end=\"2303\">PAN becoming invalid as proof of identity<br><br></p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-start=\"2305\" data-end=\"2422\">As highlighted earlier by Hindustan Times, such disruptions can significantly affect both individuals and businesses.<br><img src=\"/images/upload/blogImage/1766752057500_5ydlxut0ndh.png\"><br><br></p>\n<h4 data-start=\"2424\" data-end=\"2481\"><strong data-start=\"2429\" data-end=\"2481\">Step-by-Step Guide: How to Link PAN with Aadhaar<br><br></strong></h4>\n<p data-start=\"2483\" data-end=\"2576\">Linking your PAN with Aadhaar is a straightforward process on the Income Tax e-Filing portal:</p>\n<p data-start=\"2578\" data-end=\"2762\">Start by visiting the <strong data-start=\"2600\" data-end=\"2631\">Income Tax e-Filing website</strong> and logging in with your PAN and password. Once logged in, go to the <strong data-start=\"2701\" data-end=\"2712\">Profile</strong> section and select the <strong data-start=\"2736\" data-end=\"2754\">‘Link Aadhaar’</strong> option.<br><br></p>\n<p data-start=\"2764\" data-end=\"2984\">Enter your PAN and Aadhaar number, then choose <strong data-start=\"2811\" data-end=\"2850\">‘Continue to Pay through e-Pay Tax’</strong>. Select the relevant <strong data-start=\"2872\" data-end=\"2891\">assessment year</strong> and choose <strong data-start=\"2903\" data-end=\"2923\">‘Other Receipts’</strong> as the payment type. The applicable fee will be auto-filled.</p>\n<p data-start=\"2986\" data-end=\"3215\">Proceed to generate the challan, select your preferred payment method, and complete the payment through the redirected bank website. After successful payment, return to the e-Filing portal to complete the Aadhaar linking process.<br><br></p>\n<h4 data-start=\"3217\" data-end=\"3265\"><strong data-start=\"3222\" data-end=\"3265\">How to Check PAN–Aadhaar Linking Status<br><br></strong></h4>\n<p data-start=\"3267\" data-end=\"3401\">To check whether your PAN and Aadhaar are already linked, visit the Income Tax e-Filing portal and click on <strong data-start=\"3375\" data-end=\"3400\">‘Link Aadhaar Status’</strong>.<br><br></p>\n<p data-start=\"3403\" data-end=\"3538\">Enter your PAN and Aadhaar details and submit the request. The system will instantly display the current linking status on your screen.<br><br></p>\n<h4 data-start=\"3540\" data-end=\"3596\"><strong data-start=\"3545\" data-end=\"3596\">How to Fix Mismatched Details in PAN or Aadhaar<br><br></strong></h4>\n<p data-start=\"3598\" data-end=\"3746\">If your PAN and Aadhaar details do not match, the linking process may fail. In such cases, corrections must be made before attempting to link again.<br><br></p>\n<p data-start=\"3748\" data-end=\"3923\">For Aadhaar-related corrections, visit the <strong data-start=\"3791\" data-end=\"3807\">UIDAI portal</strong> and update your personal details. For PAN corrections, you can approach <strong data-start=\"3880\" data-end=\"3898\">Protean (NSDL)</strong> or <strong data-start=\"3902\" data-end=\"3913\">UTIITSL</strong> websites.<br><br></p>\n<p data-start=\"3925\" data-end=\"4074\">If discrepancies continue despite online corrections, biometric verification can be completed at authorised PAN service centres to resolve the issue.<br><br></p>\n<h4 data-start=\"4076\" data-end=\"4113\"><strong data-start=\"4081\" data-end=\"4113\">Don’t Wait Till the Last Day<br><br></strong></h4>\n<p data-start=\"4115\" data-end=\"4355\">With December 31, 2025 fast approaching, taxpayers are advised not to delay PAN–Aadhaar linking. Last-minute rush, payment failures, or technical errors could leave your PAN inoperative, causing avoidable stress and financial inconvenience.</p>\n<p data-start=\"4357\" data-end=\"4569\">At <strong data-start=\"4360\" data-end=\"4373\">EnsureKar</strong>, we assist individuals, professionals, and businesses with PAN–Aadhaar linking, correction services, and complete tax compliance support — ensuring your documentation stays valid and hassle-free.<br><br></p>\n<p data-start=\"4571\" data-end=\"4757\">For official coverage, you can read the full news report on <strong data-start=\"4631\" data-end=\"4650\">Hindustan Times</strong>:<br data-start=\"4651\" data-end=\"4654\">\n?<a href=\"https://www.hindustantimes.com/india-news/panaadhaar-linking-deadline-on-dec-31-heres-how-to-link-your-pan-with-aadhaar-101766661023093.html\"> <em data-start=\"4657\" data-end=\"4739\">PAN–Aadhaar linking deadline on Dec 31: Here’s how to link your PAN with Aadhaar</em> (Hindustan Times)</a></p>', 'EnsureKar Tax & Compliance Team', 'support@ensurekar.com', 'The EnsureKar Tax & Compliance Team helps individuals, startups, and businesses across India with income tax, GST, legal, and regulatory compliance. We focus on clarity, accuracy, and affordable expert support.', 'published', 0, '1766753404471_gbmvxhdpaz4.png', '/images/upload/blogImage/1766753404471_gbmvxhdpaz4.png', '[\"pan aadhaar link status\",\"aadhaar pan link status\",\"aadhar pan link\",\"aadhar card\",\"aadhar card pan card link\",\"link aadhaar status\"]', '2025-12-26 18:00:00', '2025-12-26 07:19:32', '2025-12-26 07:20:01', 0, 'PAN–Aadhaar Linking Deadline Dec 31, 2025 | How to Link & Avoid Inoperative PAN', 'PAN–Aadhaar linking deadline is December 31, 2025. Learn how to link PAN with Aadhaar, check status, fix mismatches, and avoid PAN becoming inoperative.');
